<h2 class="bac">Our Business:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Consumer and Small Business Bank (CSBB) serves more than 59 million consumer and small business households, through a distribution network that includes: 6,100 retail banking offices, 18,500 ATMs, and the nation&#39;s leading online banking offering, featuring award-winning service and nearly 30 million active users. 
</p>
<p class="bac">
The Consumer &#38; Small Business Bank Consumer MBA Banking Center Channel (BCC) Program aims to develop future Consumer Market Managers (CMM). Consumer Market Managers are regional managers responsible for driving and evaluating the performance of sales and service associates in banking centers. Recent MBA level graduates experience a 2-year general management rotational program, through 2-3 areas of the Banking Center Channel organization.   
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview:</h2>  
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Associates will initially enter the Leaders Fundamentals, Personal Banker and other targeted training programs to gain first-hand knowledge and expertise of the Banking Center Channel products and processes</li>
	<li>Associates will partner with regional sales, service and operations executives on specific, tangible initiatives rolling out across the region and/or enterprise</li>
	<li>Associate will also partner with Consumer Market executives and Consumer Market Managers to leverage best practices and implement breakthrough strategies to exceed sales/service goals
        <ul>
	<li>CMMs are responsible for leading sales and service for 10-12 banking centers in a geographic market</li>
	<li>Assess overall effectiveness of banking centers and assist in the "Structured Coaching Process” to establish and build customer relationships, deliver excellent customer treatment, manage the business and meet operational goals</li>
       </ul></li>	
	<li>Gain experience recruiting and developing world-class diverse talent, at all levels of the organization</li>
	<li>Consumer MBA rotation/assignments are carefully designed according to the developmental needs of each individual participant, and the critical needs of the business</li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Qualifications:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Ideal candidate will exhibit a strong drive for results; succeed in a fast-paced, empowered, and collaborative environment; enjoy teamwork and partnering with others; possess financial acumen, excellent organizational and strong interpersonal skills; and the ability to coach and develop associates. The ability to learn the organizational structure, the formal/informal workings of the company, and to convey a strong sense of customer and associate satisfaction to drive shareholder value is required.  
</p>
<p class="bac">
Additional requirements include: 
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>MBA graduate from an accredited business school or University</li>
	<li>Spring/Summer 2011 graduation date</li>
	<li>4&#45;7 years pre-graduate work experience involving sales, marketing and/or sales team management experience, with a demonstrated record of achievement </li>
	<li>Relevant work history that reflects experience in supervising others, delegating tasks and resolving conflicts </li>
	<li>Ability to motivate and train sales and services associates in banking centers, to grow the business and drive execution</li>
	<li>Team-building techniques to accomplish market goals</li>
	<li>Authorization to work in the United States</li>
	<li>Geographic mobility/flexibility</li>
</ul>
<p class="bac">
Preferred expertise and/or experience in at least 3 of the following:
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Ability to navigate in a highly-matrixed environment</li>
	<li>Ability to influence</li>
	<li>Previous financial services or retail experience</li>
	<li>Strong statistical/analytical background (familiarity with Six Sigma principles)</li>
	<li>Team/project management experience</li>
	<li>Strategy and/or business planning experience </li>
</ul>
<p class="bac">
Personal characteristics: 
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Strong leadership ability</li>
	<li>Ability to communicate crisply and candidly </li>
	<li>Results-oriented, proven high level of performance</li>
	<li>Ability to manage tight deadlines, organize and prioritize work independently </li>
	<li>Flexibility in exploring a variety of business areas</li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Training:</h2>
<p class="bac">
The Consumer MBA &#45; BCC Program is designed to develop future global leaders, with targeted growth for the first two years in the Banking Center Channel. Key program components include, but are not limited to: 
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Associates will be assigned to an executive, to enhance individual development and growth opportunities</li>
	<li>Rotations and assignments in various capacities within the Banking Center Channel, on-line leadership library, Six Sigma training, self directed E-learning, and targeted cross-functional team projects</li>
	<li>Specific development, coaching and training to support growth towards Banking Center Channel leadership roles</li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Locations:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Nationwide. Candidates must be geographically flexible.
</p>

